title: Hover Tooltip
modified: 20260331214738412

!! Introduction

When source position tracking is enabled, hovering over any rendered element shows a tooltip with source position information.

[img[screenshot-tooltip]]

!! What the Tooltip Shows

The tooltip displays up to three lines of information:

|! Line |! Content |! Example |
|! 1 |Source position and tiddler |`L3 @ GettingStarted` |
|! 2 |Transclusion caller chain |`← $:/core/ui/ViewTemplate/body/default` |
|! 3 |Additional callers (abbreviated) |`← $:/core/ui/ViewTemplate ← +3 more` |

!! Tooltip Behaviour

* Appears after a ''400ms hover delay'' — prevents flickering during normal mouse movement
* Shows the ''innermost'' source position — when elements are nested, the most specific match is shown
* ''Context'' (`currentTiddler`) is shown when it differs from the source tiddler — useful for list widgets where the same template renders different tiddlers
* The ''caller chain'' traces transclusion boundaries, stopping at the first non-system tiddler to avoid showing TW's internal UI template chain

!! Visual Feedback

* The hovered element gets a ''2px dashed orange outline''
* Parent outlines are ''hidden'' when a child with `data-source-pos` is hovered, so only the innermost element is highlighted
* The outline has a smooth ''150ms transition''

!! Position Format

The `data-source-pos` attribute value follows this format:

* Multi-line: `L{start}-L{end} @ tiddlerTitle`
* Single-line: `L{line} @ tiddlerTitle`

Line numbers are ''file-ready'' — they include the `.tid` file header offset (field count + blank separator line) and macro body offset, so they match exactly what your text editor shows.

